\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. S. pygmaea} (Jacq.) Sprengel, {\i Syst. Veg.}{\b  3}: 381 (1826). Stems 2-12 cm, not winged, densely leafy. Leaves sessile, 3-5(-12) mm wide, linear to linear-lanceolate, usually entire, rarely obscurely dentate. Capitula 2-3 × up to 2·5 cm, solitary, ovoid. Involucral bracts without apical appendages. 2n = 52.{\i  Mountain rocks and screes. E. Alps, W. Carpathians. }Au Cz Ge It Ju Po.
