\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. S. parviflora} (Poiret) DC.,{\i  Ann. Mus. Hist. Nat.} ({\i Paris}){\b  16}: 200 (1810). Stems 20-100 cm, narrowly winged. Basal and lower cauline leaves 20-45 mm wide, elliptical or broadly lanceolate, long-acuminate, serrate, glabrous, long-petiolate, the upper narrower and sessile. Capitula 1-1·3 cm, cylindrical, in a panicle or compact terminal corymb. Involucral bracts without apical appendages, often arachnoid-ciliate.{\i  Wet places. E. Russia.} Rs (N, C, E). ({\i Siberia.})
